package welcome;
public class PATTERN 
{
	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		// Pattern
		int i,j,n=5;
		for(i=n; i>=0; i--) 
		{
		for (j=1; j<=i; j++) 
		{
			System.out.print("* ");
		}
		System.out.println("");
		}
	}
}

OUTPUT:
* * * * * 
* * * * 
* * * 
* * 
* 

DETAILED DESCRIPTION:
The above program is used to print the inversed right angle triangle for which we use variable i and j, i denotes for columns and j denotes for rows.
when the input value enters the for loop in which (i=5;i>=0;i--) continues still 1 which is for columns and for j depends on i value(j=1;j<=1;j++)continues still the i value. 
